This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it presents a two-layered feedforward neural model that learns features in an online and unsupervised manner following the Hebbian rule. The paper also involves the use of clustering techniques, which are commonly used in neural network models. 

The paper is also likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as it discusses the development of simple and complex cell-like receptive field properties in response to natural videos acquired by a camera mounted on a cat's head. 

Additionally, the paper may belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves the learning of features and their transformations in an unsupervised manner. 

The paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it presents a neural model that can predict by learning lateral connections among the first layer neurons. 

Finally, the paper may belong to the sub-category of cs.SD (Sound) as it mentions the use of natural videos acquired by a camera mounted on a cat's head, which may involve sound.
